- A team can have multiple players;
- A player can have multiple injuries;
- The `LEFT JOIN` ensures that teams without any injuries are still listed with a count of 0.

- A "total game score" is the sum of the scores of both the home and away teams in a game;
- "Total points scored by players" refers to the aggregate points scored by all players on a team across all games;
- "Winning percentage" is calculated as the number of wins divided by the total number of games played.

- "average points per game" is calculated by dividing the total points by the number of games played;
- "highest average points per game" refers to the best performance in terms of points per game;
- "smallest ID" is used to break ties when multiple teams have the same highest average points per game.

- "High salary" refers to a total salary greater than $10,000,000;
- "Good injury record" means the player has fewer than three injuries;
- "Top-performing player" is determined by the total points scored and the number of games played.

sql:
SELECT wins, winning_percentage
FROM standings
ORDER BY winning_percentage DESC;

